**Finding the New Administrative Unit for "Xã Chi Lăng"**

Okay, so the user needs the new administrative unit for "Xã Chi Lăng, Huyện Hưng Hà, Tỉnh Thái Bình". Let's break this down systematically. First, I need to consider the province.  "Tỉnh Thái Bình" has merged with "Hưng Yên" according to "60-NQ/TW". So, we're now looking for something within "Tỉnh Hưng Yên".

My next step is to examine resolutions relevant to this new province. Specifically, I'm focusing on those about the re-arrangement of communes. I've found "1666/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của tỉnh Hưng Yên". This is promising.

Now, I'll carefully scrutinize the lines within this resolution, looking for any mention of "Chi Lăng". And there it is! The resolution *explicitly* maps "Chi Lăng" from "Huyện Hưng Hà" to the new "Xã Thần Khê". This aligns with the old address, so the confidence should be very high.

To be thorough, let me cross-reference the result. I found a new ward item for Xã Thần Khê in the new wards list. 
It says: {"ward_code":"12631","ward_name":"Xã Thần Khê","province_name":"Tỉnh Hưng Yên"}.

To ensure there's no confusion, I'm checking for alternative possibilities to make sure there are no other places called Chi Lăng in any other province that got merged into the province Hưng Yên. Based on my review, that seems to be the right conclusion.  Therefore, "Xã Chi Lăng" is now part of "Xã Thần Khê" in "Tỉnh Hưng Yên".
